# W3 System Data Contract (v0.1)

## 1. Core Entities
- module
- task
- signal
- sync-state
- decision
- boundary
- risk-flag

## 2. Mandatory Fields (Global Standard)
- id: string
- type: enum
- version: string
- owner: module-id
- created_at: timestamp
- updated_at: timestamp
- payload: object

## 3. Module → Contract Mapping
- BBX19 → directive, boundary, policy
- ChatGPT → flow, prototype, test-case
- DeepSeek → pattern/meta-structure
- Gemini → validation-output, risk-scan
- Grok → narrative, anomaly-signal
- Copilot-Gm → orchestration-log, repo-state

## 4. Payload Validation Rules
- payload MUST match module spec
- field missing → raise `error:payload.missing`
- schema drift → raise `error:schema.version_mismatch`

## 5. Sync Rules
- all modules MUST reference latest version
- sync-state = true → when all modules acknowledge same version
- conflict → create `[sync-conflict]` issue
